ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes I would recommend it, since this part of the knowledge is very useful and applied in a lot of area.

This course is helpful for students interested in biomaterials and tissue engineering. It is not hard but requires a lot of work. I would recommend to another student who is interested in gaining knowledge of this field.
I'll recommend it. And, after this class, you'll find that most of knowledge you need to know about biomaterials has already been covered in the class.That's great.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course not only introduced the basic concepts in major types of biomaterials such as structure-function relationships, but also included useful examples to help us understand the applications of those materials.
It was very applicable to my research. I found I learned a lot from this course.
